===Noun===
{{en-noun|laws|-}}

# <!--DefA--> A [[written]] or [[understood]] [[rule]] that [[concern]]s [[behaviour]]s and the [[appropriate]] [[consequence]]s [[thereof]].  Laws are usually associated with [[mores]].
# <!--DefB-->{{uncountable}} The [[body]] of rules issued by the [[legislative]] [[authority]].
# <!--DefC--> (''uncountable'') The body of rules and [[standard]]s to be applied by [[court]]s and [[similar]] authorities
# <!--DefD--> A [[one-sided]] [[contract]].
# <!--DefE--> A well-established, [[observed]] [[physical]] characteristic or behavior of nature.
#: ''Newton and Einstein understood the '''law''' of gravitation in very different ways.''
# <!--DefF-->{{mathematics}} A [[statement]] that is true under specified [[condition]]s.
# <!--DefG--> A [[category]] of [[English]] "[[common law]]" [[petition]]s that [[request]] [[monetary]] [[relief]], as opposed to relief in forms other than a monetary [[judgment]]; compare to "[[equity]]".
# <!--DefH-->{{cricket}} One of the [[official]] rules of [[cricket]] as [[codified]] by the [[MCC]].
# <!--DefI-->{{slang}} (''uncountable'') The [[police]].
#: ''Here comes the '''law''' — run!''

